<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529654>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Dorsal view of body (A, B) and frontal view of mandible (C, D) of Limnonectes rhacodus (holotype, MZB Amph 2991: A, C) and Occidozyga sp. from Matang (KUHE 53037: B, D), showing dorsum similarly with transverse wrinkles (A, B) and different mandible shape (with a median and two lateral cusps in C and with a single median cusp in D). Not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4529654/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

